Akeem Akinsanya alleged to have been shot dead in Ifo by a team of policemen attached to the Zonal Intervention Squad (ZIS), Obada Oko, Abeokuta, Ogun State, was hit by an accidentally- discharged bullet, the command said yesterday. A statement by its spokesperson, Hauwa Idris-Adamu, a Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP), said the accidental discharge occurred when suspected cultists attempted to snatch the AK47 service rifle of Inspector Sunday Ogundapo, who led the team to effect the arrest of a suspected notorious cultist, Abu, alias Regal. The police said the team was investigating a case of unlawful possession of arms, ammunition and cultism in which a suspect in custody, Afeez Popoola, alias Level, had implicated Abu. The police alleged that Abu was the carrier of arms and ammunition for the Eiye cult at Cassava Perch, Ifo. “Abu ‘Regal’ was arrested by the team around 3pm while in possession of one locally-made pistol with cartridges kept in a handbag. The items were recovered by the police team. While the team was taking the suspect to the station with the recovered items, a renowned tout popularly known as ‘Obasanjo’, in company of suspected cultists, ambushed and attacked them. “The team leader, Inspector Sunday Ogundapo, who was in possession of the recovered exhibits, was inflicted with machete injuries on the head. He was about to be dispossessed of his AK47 rifle, but in the process of struggling with the mob, a bullet was accidentally discharged, killing Akeem Akinsanya. “The remains of the deceased have been deposited at the Ifo General Hospital mortuary for postmortem, while members of the gang were arrested and are under investigation. “The public is requested to assist the police with information that will aid tracking and apprehending of these cultists and other miscreants that are terrorising innocent people,” Idris-Adamu said.